description:
Row-major dense matrix over `FieldVec<F>`. Core API: construct, index, row/col slices, transpose, dimensions. Ergonomic operator overloads (`Mul`, `Add`, `Index`). Must NOT touch `BitMatrix` (remains GF(2)-specialized).

## API sketch

```rust
pub struct FieldMatrix<F: FiniteField> {
    rows: usize,
    cols: usize,
    data: FieldVec<F>,
}

impl<F: FiniteField> FieldMatrix<F> {
    pub fn new(rows: usize, cols: usize) -> Self;
    pub fn from_rows(rows: Vec<FieldVec<F>>) -> Self;
    pub fn row(&self, i: usize) -> &[F];
    pub fn col_iter(&self, j: usize) -> impl Iterator<Item = &F>;
    pub fn transpose(&self) -> Self;
    pub fn identity(n: usize) -> Self where F: ConstField;
}
```

